Case called at 9:38am [mo]
Defendant Codell N. Miller in court with Attorney Elizabeth F. Svehlek.   ADA Monica Hall appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  
Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of " No Contest " entered; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; the Court accepts plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

ADA Hall submits a restitution request
Sentencing arguments given by Counsel
Statement made by Mr. Miller 

The Court sentences Defendant to:
--serve 5  days in Jefferson County Jail, WITHOUT Huber privileges; TIME SERVED SENTENCE
--5 days credit for time already served given
--to pay restitution in the amount of $437.60 to the City of Lake Mills; joint and several with Tyler Bostwick.
--pay costs of $243 plus $200 DNA surcharge= $443 plus $169 in subpoena fees.

The Cash bond is to be applied to the Restitution and Costs; applied first to the restitution, balance is to be applied to the court costs and subpoena fees.
After application of the Cash bond, the remaining total is $299.60; this is to be paid by 2/1/2016; non-payment shall result in a 6  day jail term with Huber privileges, consecutive
